  <main class="content">
    <!-- TAB BAR -->
    <div class="tabs" id="tabs">
      <button class="tab active" data-target="overview">Overview</button>
      <button class="tab" data-target="purchasing-factors">Purchasing Factors</button>
      <button class="tab" data-target="price-preferences">Price Preferences</button>
      <button class="tab" data-target="purchasing-channels">Purchasing Channels</button>
      <button class="tab" data-target="brand-recognition">Brand Recognition</button>
    </div>

    <!-- TAB PANELS -->
    <section id="overview" class="panel tab-panel active">
      <h2>Final Recommendation</h2>
      <p>
        Pursue a mid-range, culturally positioned high-fidelity speaker strategy,
        anchored in strong purchase intent and clear differentiation from JBL, Sony, and Bose.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="purchasing-factors" class="panel tab-panel">
      <h2>Purchasing Factors</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Sound quality and bass response ranked as the #1 decision driver.</li>
        <li>Battery life and durability are key “table stakes” for outdoor use.</li>
        <li>Brand reputation and design matter more for Gen Z than for older segments.</li>
        <li>Water resistance and portability are must-have features for frequent users.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="price-preferences" class="panel tab-panel">
      <h2>Price Preferences</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Most respondents prefer a price band of <strong>$150–$250</strong>.</li>
        <li>Above $300, stated purchase intent drops sharply.</li>
        <li>Pricing below $150 risks diluting Beats’ premium perception.</li>
        <li>Sweet spot for a Beats high-fidelity speaker: <strong>$199–$249</strong>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="purchasing-channels" class="panel tab-panel">
      <h2>Purchasing Channels</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Top channels: online marketplaces (e.g., Amazon) and official brand sites.</li>
        <li>Apple Store and carrier/retail partners are strong for in-person discovery.</li>
        <li>Students show high comfort with direct-to-consumer online purchases.</li>
        <li>Retail displays + creator reviews drive trial and conversion.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="brand-recognition" class="panel tab-panel">
      <h2>Brand Recognition</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Beats enjoys high unaided awareness among 18–24 year-olds.</li>
        <li>Perceived as stylish, bass-heavy, and culturally relevant.</li>
        <li>Seen as a lifestyle brand more than a purely technical audio brand.</li>
        <li>Strong opportunity to extend this equity into the high-fidelity speaker space.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</div>

<script>
  // Simple tab switcher
  const tabs = document.querySelectorAll(".tab");
  const panels = document.querySelectorAll(".tab-panel");

  tabs.forEach(tab => {
    tab.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const targetId = tab.getAttribute("data-target");

      // update tab states
      tabs.forEach(t => t.classList.remove("active"));
      tab.classList.add("active");

      // update panels
      panels.forEach(panel => {
        panel.classList.toggle("active", panel.id === targetId);
      });
    });
  });
</script>
